      "writtenOn": "2020-07-29T12:37:37Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "BYTES is twice as space efficient as storing a hex encoded string. encode(trace_id, \u0027hex\u0027) is handy to see the hex encoded hash when extracting the column via SQL.\n\nAdditionally, in your hand crafted queries, you can input the bytes as x\u002747109b059f45e4f9d5ab61dd0199e2c9\u0027 which will automatically be decoded from hex.\n\nhttps://skia-review.googlesource.com/c/buildbot/+/305016/12/golden/cmd/cockroachdb_explore/cockroachdb_explore.go#182",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 3,
        "startChar": 10,
        "endLine": 3,
        "endChar": 16
      },
      "revId": "cb2ee826d544a57c30773468fee33f2c070b984e",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
