    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "41f469c1_413ae5ea",
        "filename": "perf/migrations/cockroachdb/0002_create_initial_tables.up.sql",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 4,
      "author": {
        "id": 5205
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-07-29T15:22:46Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Dropped trace_name because it is redundant.\n\nI actually need both params and trace_name when building a Dataframe has both a map from trace_name to the []float32 values, and also a ParamSet which represents the sum of all the Params from all the traces in the Dataframe, so I would have to convert from params \u003c-\u003e trace_name no matter what.",
      "parentUuid": "f44d85fa_387ac2b9",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 4,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 4,
        "endChar": 11
      },
      "revId": "cb2ee826d544a57c30773468fee33f2c070b984e",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "1b2fea21_cb1748ea",
        "filename": "perf/migrations/cockroachdb/0002_create_initial_tables.up.sql",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 5,
      "author": {
        "id": 5395
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-07-29T12:37:37Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "One reason I went with JSONB over STRING[] is that I don\u0027t have to sanitize the key/values. This may not matter much in practice, but with this array format, keys should not have equal signs, as that could throw off comparison.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 5,
        "startChar": 8,
        "endLine": 5,
        "endChar": 16
      },
      "revId": "cb2ee826d544a57c30773468fee33f2c070b984e",
